    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loud humming noise with a fan that won't spin is a classic sign of a stuck capacitor or a seized motor bearing, which is a very common issue for outdoor units. It's definitely not safe to go look at it right now if you can avoid it, because the unit is likely overheating and could be a fire hazard, plus the fan blades spinning slowly or not at all can cause the compressor to overheat and shut down permanently. You should call a professional HVAC technician immediately; they have the tools to safely diagnose the electrical components and replace any faulty capacitors or bearings without risking injury or further damage to your system. While you wait for them, you can check the circuit breaker to ensure the unit hasn't tripped, but do not attempt to open the outdoor casing yourself.\n\nIf you absolutely must inspect it later, wear heavy gloves and safety glasses, as the fan blades can still spin unexpectedly if the capacitor discharges, and the motor can be surprisingly hot. You might also want to check if there are any obvious obstructions like leaves or debris blocking the fan, though a humming sound usually points to an internal electrical fault rather than a simple blockage. Remember, even a small amount of moisture in the air can cause corrosion on",
